title: For Sale:  Scammers are everywhere
postcontent: If you see a good price, it is probably too good to be true.  They list a very reasonable/realistic price and may even list a city (Jacksonville etc.) When you contact them, all they want is for you to send FFL & payment etc. Most of those who will not meet you face to face, are MOST LIKELY a scammer attempting to bait you into sending money making it all sound legit. Press on with the seller, If he does not provide a legitimate means to contact him (phone/address etc), than he is MOST LIKELY a scammer. DO NOT SEND MONEY to anyone without them revealing who they really are. There are several on here just today.

The PT22 is a .22LR semi-automatic pistol produced by Taurus and features an 8+1 round capacity magazine. The PT22 is often viewed as a Taurus copy of the Beretta 21 Bobcat due to having a similar "tip up" barrel. In fact this small pistol is very different in design and function from the Beretta. The PT22 is a cast steel frame and slide, manufactured in Florida, USA. It has a spur-less hammer, and a long but smooth double action only (DAO) trigger.
